<div2 type="body">

<p>Sir, Received your note in answer to mine of last Sunday <unclear reason="illegible">sateing</unclear> your price of Abraham to be $500 and the <del>balance of the</del> <unclear reason="illegible">year</unclear> <unclear reason="illegible">hire</unclear>, Mr Lyons will give you a fair price for your man as he think he considers him not a prime hand, prime hand can be bought for $500 Abraham is small and weakly, he has Directed me to give you 400 <del>after</del> when the money paid the hire to stop by paying for what time he has served which I believe it is most he will give if you will take that sum you will write by Abraham so that I can make the arrangement with him for the money. Am yours most Respectfully</p>

<p>Elijah Chamblin<lb/>
27th of June 1813</p>

</div2>

<pb xml:id="p002" facs="oscys.case.0081.004.002.jpg"/>

<div2 type="back">
 
<ab>Mr John Millon<lb/>
Frederick County</ab>

</div2>
 
</div1>
 
